TagHelpers.Name: Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Authorization.AuthorizeRouteView
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
             Combines the behaviors of <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Authorization.AuthorizeView" /> and <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.RouteView" />,
             so that it displays the page matching the specified route but only if the user
             is authorized to see it.
            
             Additionally, this component supplies a cascading parameter of type <see cref="T:System.Threading.Tasks.Task`1" />,
             which makes the user's current authentication state available to descendants.
             </summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fires when the data source is read. Use this to attach your own filtering logic.
            Once attached, you must implement all such data source operations here,
            the Component will no longer perform them for you.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

            </summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines the height of the DropDownList's Popup.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: PopupWidth
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines the width of the DropDownList's Popup.
            The default value is "auto", which will use the element width for the popup as well.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: PopupClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines the CSS class that will be applied to the rendered popup of the component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Filterable
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines whether data should be filtered on typing in the component.
            The data will be filtered based on the TextField.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AriaLabelledBy
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Describe the aria-labelledby attribute for the component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AriaDescribedBy
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines the aria-describedby attribute for the component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ScrollMode
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines scrolling mode of the Component. Possible values are Scrollable and Virtual.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ItemHeight
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines the height of each item in the popup. Accepts a number and is applied as pixels.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: PageSize
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines the page size of the component for virtual scrolling. Requires ScrollMode="DropDownScrollMode.Virtual".
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: TotalCount
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines the total number of items. Use only when the components is
            configured with Virtualization and OnRead event.
            Set its value according to the data source and take filtering into account.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether the Component is enabled.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
             Specifies the callback that's called when the value changes.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Value

<summary>
            Specifies the value of the input. Used with two-way binding.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: TabIndex
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The TabIndex of the component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnChange
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: RenderAs
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Sets the preferred rendering engine. If it is not supported by the browser, the Barcode will switch to the first available mode.The supported values are: "canvas" - renders the widget as a Canvas element, if available. or "svg" - renders the widget as inline SVG document, if available.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Background
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The background of the barcode area. Any valid CSS color string will work here, including hex and rgb.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Checksum
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the Barcode will display the checksum digit next to the value in the text area.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Color
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The color of the bar elements. Any valid CSS color string will work here, including hex and rgb.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Type
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The symbology (encoding) the barcode will use.The supported values are: EAN8; EAN13; UPCE; UPCA; Code11; Code39; Code39Extended; Code93; Code93Extended; Code128; Code128A; Code128B; Code128C; GS1-128; MSImod10; MSImod11; MSImod1010; MSImod1110 or POSTNET.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Value
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The initial value of the Barcode
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Width

            Sets the preferred rendering engine. If it is not supported by the browser, the Barcode will switch to the first available mode.The supported values are: "canvas" - renders the widget as a Canvas element, if available. or "svg" - renders the widget as inline SVG document, if available.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The background of the barcode area. Any valid CSS color string will work here, including hex and rgb.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Checksum
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the Barcode will display the checksum digit next to the value in the text area.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The color of the bar elements. Any valid CSS color string will work here, including hex and rgb.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Type
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The symbology (encoding) the barcode will use.The supported values are: EAN8; EAN13; UPCE; UPCA; Code11; Code39; Code39Extended; Code93; Code93Extended; Code128; Code128A; Code128B; Code128C; GS1-128; MSImod10; MSImod11; MSImod1010; MSImod1110 or POSTNET.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AxisCrossingValue
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Category index at which the first value axis crosses this axis (when set as an object).Category indices at which the value axes cross the category axis (when set as an array).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Background
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The background color of the axis.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: BaseUnitStep
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The step (interval) between categories in base units. Setting it to "auto" will set the step to such value that the total number of categories does not exceed categoryAxis.maxDateGroups.This option is ignored if categoryAxis.baseUnit is set to "fit".
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Categories
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The category names. The chart will create a category for every item of the array.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Color
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The color to apply to all axis elements. Accepts a valid CSS color string, including hex and rgb. Can be overridden by categoryAxis.labels.color andcategoryAxis.line.color.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Max
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The last date displayed on the category date axis. By default, the minimum date is the same as the last category. This is often used in combination with the categoryAxis.min and categoryAxis.roundToBaseUnit options to set up a fixed date range.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: MaxDateGroups
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The maximum number of groups (categories) to display whencategoryAxis.baseUnit is set to "fit" orcategoryAxis.baseUnitStep is set to "auto".
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Min
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The first date displayed on the category date axis. By default, the minimum date is the same as the first category. This is often used in combination with the categoryAxis.min and categoryAxis.roundToBaseUnit options to set up a fixed date range.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Name
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The unique axis name. Used to associate a series with a category axis using the series.categoryAxis option.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: StartAngle
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The angle (degrees) of the first category on the axis.Angles increase clockwise and zero is to the left. Negative values are acceptable.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Visible
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the chart will display the category axis. By default the category axis is visible.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: WeekStartDay
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The week start day when categoryAxis.baseUnit is set to "weeks".The supported values are: kendo.days.Sunday - equal to 0; kendo.days.Monday - equal to 1; kendo.days.Tuesday - equal to 2; kendo.days.Wednesday - equal to 3; kendo.days.Thursday - equal to 4; kendo.days.Friday - equal to 5 or kendo.days.Saturday - equal to 6.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: BaseUnit
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the base time interval for the axis.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Type
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the category axis type.
            </summary>

TagHelpers.Name: Telerik.Blazor.Components.ChartCategoryAxisLabels
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            Telerik UI ChartCategoryAxisLabels.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Background
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The background color of the labels. Accepts a valid CSS color string, including hex and rgb.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Color
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The text color of the labels. Accepts a valid CSS color string, including hex and rgb.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Font
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The font style of the labels. Accepts a valid CSS color string, for example "20px 'Courier New'".
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Format
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The format used to display the labels. Uses kendo.format. Contains one placeholder ("{0}") which represents the category value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Mirror
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the chart will mirror the axis labels and ticks. If the labels are normally on the left side of the axis, mirroring the axis will render them to the right.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Skip
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The number of labels to skip. By default no labels are skipped.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Step
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The label rendering step - render every n-th label. By default every label is rendered.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Template
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The template which renders the labels.The fields which can be used in the template are: value - the category value; dataItem - the data item, in case a field has been specified. If the category does not have a corresponding item in the data then an empty object will be passed.; format - the default format of the label or culture - the default culture (if set) on the label.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Visible
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the chart will display the category axis labels. By default the category axis labels are visible.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Position
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the position of the labels.
            </summary>

<summary>
            The X offset of the chart legend. The offset is relative to the default position of the legend. For instance, a value of 20 will move the legend 20 pixels to the right of its initial position. A negative value will move the legend to the left of its current position.

BoundAttributes.Name: Template
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The template which renders the chart series label.The fields which can be used in the template are: category - the category name. Available for area, bar, column, bubble, donut, line, pie and waterfall series.; dataItem - the original data item used to construct the point. Will be null if binding to array.; percentage - the point value represented as a percentage value. Available only for donut, pie and 100% stacked charts.; series - the data series; stackValue - the cumulative point value on the stack. Available only for stackable series.; value - the point value.             </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: BaseUnit
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The base time interval for the axis labels. The default baseUnit is determined automatically from the value range. Available options: milliseconds; seconds; minutes; hours; days; weeks; months or years.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Categories
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The category names. Applicable for charts with X and Y category axes (heatmap).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The color of the axis. Accepts a valid CSS color string, including hex and rgb.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: MajorUnit
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The interval between major divisions. If this is a date axis the value represents the number of xAxis.baseUnits between major divisions. If the xAxis.type is set to "log", the majorUnit value will be used for the base of the logarithm.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Max
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The maximum value of the axis.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Min
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The minimum value of the axis.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: MinorUnit
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The interval between minor divisions. It defaults to 1/5 of the xAxis.majorUnit. If the xAxis.type is set to "log", the minorUnit value represents the number of divisions between two major units and defaults to the major unit minus one.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Name
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The unique axis name. Used to associate a series with a x axis using the series.xAxis option.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: NarrowRange
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the chart will prevent the automatic axis range from snapping to 0. Setting it to false will force the automatic axis range to snap to 0.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Reverse
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the value axis direction will be reversed. By default values increase from left to right and from bottom to top.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: StartAngle
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The angle (degrees) where the 0 value is placed. Applicable to polar series.Angles increase counterclockwise and zero is to the right. Negative values are acceptable.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AxisCrossingValue
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Value at which the Y axis crosses this axis. (Only for object)Value indices at which the Y axes cross the value axis. (Only for array)Date at which the Y axis crosses this axis. (Only for date)
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Background
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The background color of the axis.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: BaseUnit
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The base time interval for the axis labels. The default baseUnit is determined automatically from the value range. Available options: milliseconds; seconds; minutes; hours; days; weeks; months or years.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Categories
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The category names. Applicable for charts with X and Y category axes (heatmap).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Color
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The color of the axis. Accepts a valid CSS color string, including hex and rgb.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: MajorUnit
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The interval between major divisions. If this is a date axis the value represents the number of xAxis.baseUnits between major divisions. If the yAxis.type is set to "log", the majorUnit value will be used for the base of the logarithm.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Max
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The maximum value of the axis.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Min
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The minimum value of the axis.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: MinorUnit
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The interval between minor divisions. It defaults to 1/5 of the yAxis.majorUnit. If the yAxis.type is set to "log", the minorUnit value represents the number of divisions between two major units and defaults to the major unit minus one.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Name
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The unique axis name. Used to associate a series with a y axis using the series.yAxis option.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: NarrowRange
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the chart will prevent the automatic axis range from snapping to 0. Setting it to false will force the automatic axis range to snap to 0.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Reverse
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the value axis direction will be reversed. By default values increase from left to right and from bottom to top.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Type
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The axis type.The supported values are: "numeric" - numeric axis.; "date" - specialized axis for displaying chronological data. or "log" - logarithmic axis..
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Visible
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the chart will display the y axis. By default the y axis is visible.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AxisCrossingValue
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Value at which the Y axis crosses this axis. (Only for object)Value indices at which the Y axes cross the value axis. (Only for array)Date at which the Y axis crosses this axis. (Only for date)
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Background
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The background color of the labels. Accepts a valid CSS color string, including hex and rgb.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Color
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The text color of the labels. Accepts a valid CSS color string, including hex and rgb.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Font
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The font style of the labels. Accepts a valid CSS color string, for example "20px 'Courier New'".
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Format
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The format used to display the labels. Uses kendo.format. Contains one placeholder ("{0}") which represents the category value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Mirror
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the chart will mirror the axis labels and ticks. If the labels are normally on the left side of the axis, mirroring the axis will render them to the right.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Skip
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The number of labels to skip.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Step
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The label rendering step - render every n-th label. By default every label is rendered.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Template
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The template which renders the labels.The fields which can be used in the template are: value - the category value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Visible
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the chart will display the y axis labels. By default the y axis labels are visible.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Position
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the position of the labels.
            </summary>

            The hint that is shown if no item is selected.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AllowCustom
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines whether custom values to be allowed in the ComboBox.
            By defaut, the ComboBox dismisses values that do not appear in the supplied list of items.
            When true, ComboBox behaves as TextBox. Meaning that typeof(Value) should be string.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ClearButton
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines whether to render a clear button in the ComboBox.
            Clear Button is displayed on hover when the ComboBox has value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines the filter operator. Default value is StringFilterOperator.StartsWith.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnRead
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fires when the data source is read. Use this to attach your own filtering logic.
            Once attached, you must implement all such data source operations here,
            the Component will no longer perform them for you.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ValueMapper
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A callback function that returns an item that corresponds to the argument value.
            Used in VirtualScrollingn combined with OnRead to facilitate pre-selection
            of items that are not currently loaded.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Background
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The background color of the QR code. Accepts a valid CSS color string, including hex and rgb.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Color
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The color of the QR code. Accepts a valid CSS color string, including hex and rgb.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Encoding
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The encoding mode used to encode the value.The possible values are: "ISO_8859_1" - supports all characters from the ISO/IEC 8859-1 character set. or "UTF_8" - supports all Unicode characters..
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ErrorCorrection
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The error correction level used to encode the value.The possible values are: "L" - approximately 7% of the codewords can be restored.; "M" - approximately 15% of the codewords can be restored.; "Q" - approximately 25% of the codewords can be restored. or "H" - approximately 30% of the codewords can be restored..
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Padding
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Sets the minimum distance in pixels that should be left between the border and the QR modules.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: RenderAs
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Sets the preferred rendering engine. If it is not supported by the browser, the QRCode will switch to the first available mode.The supported values are: "canvas" - renders the widget as a Canvas element, if available. or "svg" - renders the widget as inline SVG document, if available.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Size
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the size of a QR code in pixels (i.e. "200px").
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Value
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The value of the QRCode.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Width
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the width of the component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Height
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the height of the component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Class
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The CSS class that will be rendered on the component's wrapping element.
            </summary>

The function return value is displayed instead of the individual points.The supported values are: "avg" - the average of all values for the date period.; "count" - the number of values for the date period.; "max" - the highest value for the date period.; "min" - the lowest value for the date period.; "sum" - the sum of all values for the date period. Defaults to 0 if no data points are defined.; "sumOrNull" - the sum of all values for the date period. Defaults to null if no data points are defined.; "first" - the first value; function(values, series, dataItems, category) - user-defined aggregate function. TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers.ITagHelper" /> implementation targeting elements containing attributes with URL expected values.
            </summary>
            <remarks>Resolves URLs starting with '~/' (relative to the application's 'webroot' setting) that are not
            targeted by other <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers.ITagHelper" />s. Runs prior to other <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers.ITagHelper" />s to ensure
            application-relative URLs are resolved.</remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-fallback-src-include
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A comma separated list of globbed file patterns of JavaScript scripts to fallback to in the case the
            primary one fails.
            The glob patterns are assessed relative to the application's 'webroot' setting.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-fallback-src-exclude
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A comma separated list of globbed file patterns of JavaScript scripts to exclude from the fallback list, in
            the case the primary one fails.
            The glob patterns are assessed relative to the application's 'webroot' setting.
            Must be used in conjunction with <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.ScriptTagHelper.FallbackSrcInclude" />.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-fallback-test
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The script method defined in the primary script to use for the fallback test.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-validation-summary
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If <see cref="F:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Rendering.ValidationSummary.All" /> or <see cref="F:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Rendering.ValidationSummary.ModelOnly" />, appends a validation
            summary. Otherwise (<see cref="F:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Rendering.ValidationSummary.None" />, the default), this tag helper does nothing.
            </summary>

            <c>(ValidationSummary)23</c>.
            </exception>

TagHelpers.Name: Bind
TagHelpers.Documentation: Binds the provided expression to an attribute and a change event, based on the naming of the bind attribute. For example: @bind-value="..." and @bind-value:event="onchange" will assign the current value of the expression to the 'value' attribute, and assign a delegate that attempts to set the value to the 'onchange' attribute.

BoundAttributes.Name: @bind-...
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Binds the provided expression to an attribute and a change event, based on the naming of the bind attribute. For example: @bind-value="..." and @bind-value:event="onchange" will assign the current value of the expression to the 'value' attribute, and assign a delegate that attempts to set the value to the 'onchange' attribute.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: format
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies a format to convert the value specified by the corresponding bind attribute. For example: @bind-value:format="..." will apply a format string to the value specified in @bind-value="...". The format string can currently only be used with expressions of type DateTime.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: event
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies the event handler name to attach for change notifications for the value provided by the '@bind-...' attribute.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: culture
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies the culture to use for conversions.
